<BODY>
<HEADLINE> "Shanghai Five" Nations Vow to Safeguard Regional Security </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DUSHANBE, Tajikistan, July 5 (Xinhua) -- Presidents of the "
Shanghai Five" nations pledged here Wednesday to join efforts in
safeguarding regional security, and urged peaceful solution to all
regional conflicts under the framework of the United Nations.
</P>
<P>
The presidents of China, Tajikistan, Russia, Kyrgyzstan and
Kazakhstan made the statement at their one-day meeting, commonly
known as the "Shanghai Five" summit.
</P>
<P>
In the statement, the presidents expressed deep concern over
the situation in Afghanistan, regarding it as a serious threat to
world peace and regional stability.
</P>
<P>
They supported the efforts and dominating role of the U.N. in
political settlement of the Afghan issue, and urged all
conflicting parties to exert utmost restraint and conduct peace
talks by taking into consideration the interests of all parties
and strata in Afghanistan.
</P>
<P>
Expressing their satisfaction with the progress made in
Tajikistan's peace and national reconciliation, the presidents
called for more international assistance to the country and
reaffirmed their support for its efforts in post-war
reconstruction, social reform, as well as its economic and
democratic development.
</P>
<P>
The five nations agreed to open up political dialogue channels
to promote mutual trusts and to further enhance multilateral
cooperation in maintaining regional peace and stability. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
