<DOCNO> XIE20000706.0006 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> "Shanghai Five" Nations Agree to Strengthen Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DUSHANBE, Tajikistan, July 5 (Xinhua) -- The "Shanghai Five"
nations agreed here Wednesday to strengthen cooperation between
them in the fields of trade, culture, environmental protection and
foreign affairs.
</P>
<P>
The five nations, namely China, Russia, Kazakhstan, Tajikistan
and Kyrgyzstan, said in a joint statement following the annual "
Shanghai Five" summit, that they will further improve economic and
trade partnership among them in line with the principle of
equality and mutually beneficial cooperation.
</P>
<P>
They promised to improve their internal investment and trade
environment respectively in an effort to create favorable
conditions for normal business activities between businessmen and
companies from each other and for proper solutions to trade
disputes between them, the statement said.
</P>
<P>
Russia, Kazakhstan, Tajikistan and Kyrgyzstan expressed their
support for China's invitation of Russia and the Central Asian
nations to participate in the development of China's western part.
</P>
<P>
The five nations will encourage the development of cultural
cooperation among them. For this purpose, they regarded it proper
to hold a meeting of cultural ministers of the five nations.
</P>
<P>
The five nations agreed to conduct bilateral as well as
multilateral cooperation in the field of environmental protection,
including the protection of water resources in this region,
according to the statement.
</P>
<P>
All parties attach great importance to the cooperation among
the foreign ministries of the five nations. They agreed that
annual meetings of foreign ministers of the five countries should
be held to tackle issues on mutual cooperation in various fields
and to discuss international and regional situation, and to
coordinate each other's stand.
</P>
<P>
The five nations will provide all possible support to the
coordinator appointed by each country. They supported the
establishment of a coordinators'council and the adoption of
constitutional documents aimed at increasing the council's work
efficiency. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
