<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Popov Reclaims European 100m Freestyle Champion </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HELSINKI, July 5 (Xinhua) -- Russian star Alexander Popov beat
Dutchman Pieter van den Hoogenband and other rivals to reclaim his
European 100 meters freestyle champion on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Van den Hoogenband outclassed Popov at last year's European
championships in Istanbul, ending a run of four 100m freestyle
titles and three 50m freestyle wins in the competition.
</P>
<P>
Popov, who clocked 48.34 seconds -- the third-fastest time ever-
- in Tuesday's semi-finals, took the final in more relaxed fashion.
</P>
<P>
Popov registered first in 48.61, with Van den Hoogenband taking
the silver in 48.77, reversing last year's order.
</P>
<P>
Popov improved the 10-year-old 50m freestyle world record and
twice coming within a whisker of his own six-year-old 100m
freestyle world mark of 48.21 -- 48.27 in last month's Russian
championships and 48.34 in Tuesday's semi-finals here. 
</P>
</TEXT>
