<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Attempt to Hijack Jordanian Plane Foiled </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
AMMAN, July 5 (Xinhua) -- Jordanian security forces foiled an
attempt to hijack a Royal Jordanian plane en route to Damascus on
Wednesday, killing one hijacker who held a Syrian passport and
injuring the other two.
</P>
<P>
Seven passengers and a security guard were also wounded in the
crossfire between the security forces and the three hijackers, a
source from Queen Alia Airport in Amman said.
</P>
<P>
He said the other two hijackers "could also be Syrian
nationals".
</P>
<P>
The incident occurred at about 10:00 p.m. local time (1900 GMT)
and 84 passengers were on board the plane. No further information
is available so far. 
</P>
</TEXT>
