<DOCNO> XIE20000706.0014 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> UN Team Arrives in Ethiopia to Facilitate Peace Pact </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, July 5 (Xinhua) -- A United Nations delegation has
arrived here to help implement the ceasefire agreement between
Ethiopia and Eritrea.
</P>
<P>
The delegation, which arrived Tuesday night, aims at
formulating a concept of operation for a possible United Nations
Peace Keeping Operation (UN/PKO) to assist the implementation of
the agreement.
</P>
<P>
The UN delegation is due to meet with the diplomatic community,
UN agencies and humanitarian organizations in both Ethiopia and
Eritrea.
</P>
<P>
The team is expected to fly to Asmara, Eritrea, on Friday for a
similar purpose.
</P>
<P>
Prior to that, it will also confer with representative of the
Organization of African Unity (OAU), which will provide two
experts to join the team.
</P>
<P>
Last month Ethiopia and Eritrea signed a cessation of
hostilities agreement brokered by the OAU, but the border dispute
which sparked the two- year-old conflict has yet to be resolved.
</P>
</TEXT>
