<HEADLINE> EU to Provide 20 Mln Euro Aid for Congo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, July 6 (Xinhua) -- The European Union (EU) will
provide 20 million euro humanitarian aid for victims of conflict
in Congo, the European Commission said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The European Commission, the EU's executive body, has approved
the funding for humanitarian operations through non-governmental
organizations and the United Nations High Commissioner for
Refugees (UNHCR).
</P>
<P>
Concerned bodies will deliver emergency assistance to
vulnerable populations in the Democratic Republic of Congo over
the next eight months. Relief will be provided to vulnerable
population groups suffering the consequences of conflict.
</P>
<P>
The EU commission said focus will be on support to health
centers, epidemiological surveillance, nutritional programs, water
and sanitation, rehabilitation of basic infrastructure.
</P>
<P>
Main objectives of this program are to support strategically
chosen health districts nationwide, including an epidemiological
surveillance system, maintenance of the caseload of 45,000 Angolan
refugees, a nutritional program for vulnerable groups in urban
settings or in specific rural areas, provision of potable water,
and recent displaced families as well as those displaced ready to
return home. 
