<HEADLINE> Chirac Urges French to Vote for Shortening Presidential Term </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 6 (Xinhua) -- French President Jacques Chirac
Thursday called on the French population to vote for the
shortening of the seven-year presidential term to five years in a
referendum to be held on September 24.
</P>
<P>
"The reduction of seven years to five years of the presidential
mandate will give our country a better democratic respiration," he
said in a statement broadcast on radio and television.
</P>
<P>
"A five-year term will let people participate more often --
personally and directly -- in public debate. In an epoch marked by
the profound and rapid changes everywhere, in France, in Europe
and in the world, it will adapt our institutions to the rhythms of
our time," said Chirac.
</P>
<P>
Chirac first announced the plan to shorten the presidential
term one month ago after most of France's political parties and
public opinions approved such an amendment of the Constitution of
the 5th Republic drafted under General de Gaulle in 1962.
</P>
<P>
The French parliament has also approved the government draft
law on the reform. 
