contribution to the economy has climbed from a paltry 10 percent
in 1990 to 39 percent in 1999.
</P>
<P>
The export board predicts a further boost in the sector to
achieve its set target of 400 million U.S. dollars in a few years
time.
</P>
<P>
"This justifies the importance that government has placed on
non- traditional exports, especially after realizing that copper
as a traditional export is not an everlasting foreign exchange
earner for the country," says the board.
</P>
<P>
Key players in the NTE sector include spinning mills, cotton,
sugar, coffee and metal. 
