Israeli-Palestinian final-status talks and reach a framework
agreement ahead of a September target for a final peace deal.
</P>
<P>
The NRP, a right-wing party, strongly opposes Barak to transfer
more territories to the Palestinians.
</P>
<P>
Ysrael Ba'aliya, Barak's another partner with four Knesset
members, has also decided to resign from the coalition ahead of the
summit.
</P>
<P>
