Thursday Berlin welcomes the upcoming visit of the Iranian
president, IRNA reported.
</P>
<P>
In an interview broadcast on Channel two of the German TV,
Fischer dismissed as "unjustified and meaningless" the demands of
some members of parliament that Khatami's visit to Germany be
cancelled, the report said.
</P>
<P>
He also expressed hope that Khatami's visit to Germany will
serve to strengthen the reform movement in Iran.
</P>
<P>
Fischer paid a visit to Iran in March following the country's
parliamentary election, in which reformers won an overwhelming
victory over their conservative rivals.
</P>
<P>
The visit came two months after Iran and Germany finally ended a
long-running legal and diplomatic dispute which caused tension in
the two countries' traditionally good trade relations.
</P>
<P>
The dispute began after a German court in 1997 accused Iran of
involvement in the assassination of exiled Iranian dissidents and
Iran arrested a German businessman accused of having illegal sex
relations with an Iranian woman. 
