<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, July 6 (Xinhua) -- Palestinian leader Yasser Arafat will
visit Cairo within the coming few days before flying to Washington
to attend the July 11 summit with Israeli and U.S. leaders, said
Egyptian Foreign Minister Amr Moussa Thursday.
</P>
<P>
U.S. President Bill Clinton announced on Wednesday Arafat and
Israeli Prime Minister Ehud Barak will meet with him on Tuesday in
the presidential retreat of Camp David to try to reach a final
peace agreement by mid-September.
</P>
<P>
Arafat, a frequent visitor to Cairo, is expected to coordinate
stances with Egyptian President Hosni Mubarak and seek his advice
on the negotiations with Israel for a final settlement of the
thorniest issues including borders, Jerusalem, Jewish settlements
and Palestinian refugees.
</P>
<P>
