<HEADLINE> Beijing Technology Zone Opens Office in Silicon Valley </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 6 (Xinhua) -- The Beijing-based Zhongguancun
Technology Zone has opened a liaison office in Silicon Valley in
the U.S. state of California, hoping to facilitate cooperation
between the zone and the Silicon Valley.
</P>
<P>
As the first link between a China-based technology zone the
American high-tech region, the new office is mainly designed to
promote the image of Zhongguancun in the U.S. and attract more
trained personnel to start high-tech businesses in the Beijing
zone.
</P>
<P>
A dearth of high-caliber professionals is a major obstacle to
building the Zhongguancun Technology Zone into a world-level park
for technological ventures, said Liu Zhihua, vice mayor of Beijing.
</P>
<P>
America's Silicon Valley is home to more than 7,000 high-tech
firms. More than 20 of the world's top 100 high-tech firms have
landed in the zone. 
</P>
</TEXT>
