<HEADLINE> Exports Rise 8.7 Percent in Pakistan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, July 6 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan's exports during fiscal
year 1999-2000 amounted to 8.46 billion U.S. dollars, 8.7 percent
higher over that of 7.78 billion dollars in the preceding year,
figures released here by the Ministry of Commerce showed Thursday.
</P>
<P>
In rupee terms, the exports during July 1999-June 2000
increased by 12.2 percent to 437.95 billion rupees against that of
390.34 billion rupees in 1998-1999.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the imports in 1999-2000 totaled 10.18 billion
dollars as against that of 9.43 billion dollars in the preceding
year, also recording an increase of 8.7 percent.
</P>
<P>
In the month of June 2000, the total exports stood at 766
million dollars as against 760 million in May, showing an rise of
0.8 percent.
</P>
<P>
The imports in June were recorded at 888 million dollars, 6.8
percent lower compared with 953 million dollars in the preceding
month. 
</P>
</TEXT>
