<DOCNO> XIE20000706.0097 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Car Blast Kills Two Russian Policemen in Dagestan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, July 6 (Xinhua) -- A car explosion killed two policemen
in Makhachkala, capital of the Russian republic of Dagestan
bordering Chechnya, on Thursday, reported the Interfax news agency.
</P>
<P>
The two Dagestani police officers were killed on the spot and a
third was injured when their Niva-make car exploded suddenly at
around 1:00 a.m. Thursday morning Moscow time (2200 GMT Wednesday)
in the third Ordzhonikidze street of the city, Interfax cited a
Dagestani Interior Ministry duty officer as saying.
</P>
<P>
The two officers who were in the car have already been
identified, parts of their bodies were collected at the scene of
the explosion, Makhachkala Prosecutor Sultan Salautdinov told
reporters.
</P>
<P>
The wounded, Senior Sergeant Salam Abdulayev, serving with
Dagestan's highest post and patrol service, was taken to the
hospital, where he was diagnosed with "a mild concussion and minor
injuries to the face and body," said the prosecutor.
</P>
<P>
The vehicle was privately owned and two Makarov pistols and
fragments of a third one were found at the scene, said the police.
</P>
<P>
The Dagestan Prosecutor's office has initiated a criminal case
about the illegal storage of explosives.
</P>
<P>
However, experts working at the scene didn't rule out the
possibility of an act of terrorism by explosive device or an
accident in the transportation of explosives, according to a live
report of Russia's NTV television.
</P>
<P>
An investigation is still underway. 
</P>
</TEXT>
