</P>
<P>
-- With talks between Israel and the Palestinians at an impasse,
U.S. President Bill Clinton announced Wednesday that the leaders
of both camps have agreed to join him next week for a secluded
summit meeting aimed at forging a final settlement of their 52-
year conflict.
</P>
<P>
-- After years of debate and delay, more than 40 countries
Wednesday pledged 320 million U.S. dollars to lay to rest the
ruined Chernobyl nuclear reactor in a huge concrete tomb. The
promised money removed the last major obstacle to the safe
shutdown of a facility -- built in Ukraine during the Soviet era --
that spewed radiation over much of Europe 14 years ago in the
world's most serious nuclear accident.
</P>
