<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Henan Oilfield Produces 50 Million Tons of Crude </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 6 (Xinhua) -- The Henan Oilfield, one of the
major oil production bases in central China, has cumulatively
turned out some 50 million tons of crude oil in its history of
over 20 years, according to today's China Petroleum News.
</P>
<P>
The paper said that the development of the oilfield started in
1978. It has so far achieved a total industrial output value of
over 18.54 billion yuan, and turned over to the state some 2.5
billion yuan in taxes and profits.
</P>
<P>
Over the past 20 years, the Henan Oilfield has discovered 15
oil deposits in the Nanyang Basin of the province and in the
Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region, and it has verified oil reserves
totaling 240 million tons.  
</P>
</TEXT>
