<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Genome Project Gets Enthusiastic Support </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 6 (Xinhua) -- Chinese scientists' successful
involvement in the global Human Genome Project (HGP) has prompted
enthusiasm at home for this type of research, according to a
Chinese researcher.
</P>
<P>
Professor Yang Huanming, director of the HGP Center under the
Genetics Institute of the Chinese Academy of Sciences (CAS),
expressed his gratitude here today to the Leqing city government
in east China's Zhejiang Province, which provided eight million
yuan (about one million U.S. dollars) in loans to the center to
aid their HGP research.
</P>
<P>
Only with the loan and broad support from society were Chinese
scientists able to complete their mission in the global effort to
decode the genome, said Yang, chief scientist of the HGP in China.
</P>
<P>
In the just-revealed first rough map of the HGP, Chinese
scientists completed one percent of the sequencing of the human
genome, but the significance of that one percent was great, Yang
pointed out.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Shunyi County, north of Beijing, where the HGP
center is located, has provided the center with 3,800 sq m of land
near the Capital International Airport for free use for two years.
</P>
<P>
Scientists at a meeting here today suggested that more local
governments and entities be encouraged to back key scientific
research projects. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000706.0114 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Central Finance Revenue Rose Last Year: Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 6 (Xinhua) -- China's finance minister, Xiang
Huaicheng, said today that the central financial revenue continued
to increase in 1999, as the national economy and social
undertakings across the country saw marked achievements.
</P>
<P>
In 1999, the central financial revenue amounted to 644.734
billion yuan, up 17.5 percent from the previous year, the total
expenditures were 823.894 billion yuan, up 27.8 percent from the
previous year.
</P>
<P>
This results in a deficit of 179.16 billion yuan, 1.143 billion
yuan less than the goal of 180.303 billion yuan approved by the
National People's Congress (NPC), the nation's highest lawmaking
body, said the minister in his report this afternoon to the
ongoing 16th Session of the Ninth NPC Standing Committee.
</P>
<P>
Xiang attributed the achievements to the pro-active fiscal
policy adopted by the Chinese government and the reform of the
central financial budget administration system.
</P>
<P>
Xiang said that in 1999 the central financial budget was based
on the budgets of various ministries which were based on those
worked out by various grassroots units, which proved to be more
efficient, scientific and comprehensive. "This way of making the
budget not only simplifies the procedures, but also benefits the
supervision and implementation of the budget," he noted.
</P>
<P>
The minister also presented the ministry's working plan for the
second half of this year.
</P>
<P>
"The ministry will continue to bring its new fiscal policy into
full play to boost economic development," he stressed.
</P>
<P>
He also in his report called for strengthening taxation work,
budget administration reform and supervision of finance work.
</P>
</TEXT>
