<HEADLINE> NE City Awards Businesses Credit Certificates </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, July 6 (Xinhua) -- A hundred and eighty-nine
businesses in this capital of the northeast province of Liaoning,
received "certificates of credit" today from the municipal
government.
</P>
<P>
All the businesses have had a good record for abiding by
contracts and been trustworthy over the past five to ten years,
according to government officials.
</P>
<P>
This is the first in the city that businesses have been awarded
"certificates of credit" from the government.
</P>
<P>
As an old industrial base with numerous enterprises, the city
of Shenyang has done a lot to help businesses to value the
importance of credit and abiding by contracts.
</P>
<P>
Each year, the government selects the best ones from among
thousands of local businesses, and they are then publicly cited
and promoted.
</P>
<P>
This has played a positive role in helping businesses to
accumulate credit, improve their public images and win more market
shares, the officials said. 
</P>
