<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Blitz On Prostitution, Gambling, Drugs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 6 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese government has launched
a nationwide crackdown on prostitution, gambling and drug abuse at
venues of public recreation.
</P>
<P>
A circular issued by the State Council said that for quite some
time, social ills such as prostitution and gambling have been
unchecked in some recreational places, which has aroused great
concern among the general public.
</P>
<P>
In the next three months, special efforts will be undertaken to
strengthen supervision of recreational places, according to the
circular.
</P>
<P>
The number of barber shops, sauna centers and massage parlors
will be sharply reduced to check the spread of social ills, which
also pose a threat to the healthy growth of young people,
according to the circular. 
</P>
</TEXT>
