<HEADLINE> Beijing Brings Order to Used Car Market (Recast) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 6 (Xinhua) -- The Beijing Zhonglian Used Car
Market opened here today, indicating a start for the reform of
second-hand vehicle deals.
</P>
<P>
The market, with the car agent company overseeing the full
purchase process, operates differently than traditional car sales
companies.
</P>
<P>
Jointly funded by the Beijing Automobile Market Management
Center, the Beijing Heng Wu Automobile Company and the Beijing
Zhonglian Automobile Market, the new second-hand vehicle market
covers an area of 900,000 square meters.
</P>
<P>
Sun Jiansheng, director in charge of the automobile management
under the local industrial and commercial bureau, noted that
Beijing now has two used vehicle businesses and will set up a
third soon.
</P>
<P>
The first used car market was set up in Beijing in 1985. In the
past decade, the business volume of the city's second-hand
vehicles increased to nearly 60,000 in 1999 from some 1,000
vehicles in 1985.  
</P>
</TEXT>
