<HEADLINE> China to Provide Loan for Fertilizer Plant in Bangladesh </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, July 6 (Xinhua) -- Bangladesh will receive a soft loan
of 53.29 million U.S. dollars from the Chinese government and a
Chinese company to implement a fertilizer project in Chittagong,
the second largest city in the country, according to a contract
signed here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Under the contract signed between China National Complete Plant
Import and Export Corporation Limited (COMPLANT) and Bangladesh
Chemical Industries Corporation, the Chinese government will
provide an interest-subsidized preferential loan of 200 million
RMB yuan (24.18 million U.S. dollars), and the COMPLANT will
provide 29.11 million dollars on seller's export credit.
</P>
<P>
The di-ammonium phosphate fertilizer plant with a production
capacity of 240,000 tons annually to be constructed in the end of
this year is expected to go into operation in 30 months.
</P>
<P>
When meeting with the COMPLANT leaders after the signing of the
contract, Bangladeshi Industries Minister Tofail Ahmed hoped China
could provide more cooperation and help in the agricultural field.
</P>
<P>
Referring to the fertilizer plant, the minister said Bangladesh
is eager to see the project be implemented as soon as possible to
meet future fertilizer needs. 
</P>
</TEXT>
