<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Germany Upsets South Africa for World Cup Victory </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, July 6 (Xinhua) -- Germany had the last smile on
Thursday as they won the right to host the 2006 World Cup finals
by a single vote.
</P>
<P>
Germany won 12 votes from FIFA's 24-member executive committee
to 11 for South Africa with one abstention in a third and final
round of voting.
</P>
<P>
Germany and South Africa both polled 11 votes after the first
two rounds which saw the other two candidates Morocco and England
eliminated.
</P>
<P>
Morocco crashed out in the first round after polling just three
votes. England received five, South Africa six and Germany 10.
</P>
<P>
In the second round Germany and South Africa both polled 11
with England two and therefore out of the running.
</P>
<P>
In the neck-and-neck struggle only one of England's votes went
to Germany in the third and final round, the other being an
abstention.
</P>
<P>
Had the vote been 12-12, Blatter would have had a casting vote.
Most people expected him to give it to South Africa. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
