<DOCNO> XIE20000706.0134 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Rain Eases North China Droughts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 6 (Xinhua) -- Strong precipitation over the past
few days has alleviated the drought in north China, but the region
is still short of water, the State Flood Control and Drought
Relief Headquarters said here today.
</P>
<P>
From July 3 to 6, much of the region received 25 to 50 mm of
rain. Parts of Beijing and Hebei got as much as 200 mm of rain.
</P>
<P>
The rain has greatly improved the soil moisture content, and
will benefit the growth of autumn crops, said officials at the
headquarters.
</P>
<P>
As the precipitation has been short and the drought severe,
some parts of the region are still facing shortages of drinking
water.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that over the past six months, rainfall in much
of north China has been 20 to 60 percent less than in normal years.
</P>
</TEXT>
