<HEADLINE> Top Lawmakers Hear Budget, Audit Reports </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 6 (Xinhua) -- Participants at the 16th Session of
the Standing Committee of the Ninth National People's Congress (
NPC) convened here this afternoon again to review reports on the
central finance budget and audit.
</P>
<P>
Li Peng, chairman of the NPC, the nation's highest lawmaking
body, attended the meeting, which was presided over by NPC Vice-
Chairman Jiang Chunyun.
</P>
<P>
Finance Minister Xiang Huaicheng delivered a report on the
central finance budget.
</P>
<P>
According to Xiang, in 1999, the central finance revenue
amounted to 644.734 billion yuan, up 17.5 percent over the
previous year, and the total expenditure was 823.894 billion yuan,
up 27.8 percent over the previous year, thus resulting in a
deficit of 179.16 billion yuan, 1.143 billion yuan less than the
1999 budgeted deficit approved by the NPC.
</P>
<P>
Li Jinhua, the country's top auditor, began his report by
praising the financial departments for implementation of the
central budget and their contribution to the reform, development
and stability, but then turned out to complain that some of these
departments had been involved in wrongdoing and illegal activities.
</P>
<P>
NPC Vice-Chairman Buhe gave a report on the inspection of the
implementation of the Law on Township Enterprises.
</P>
<P>
In addition, written reports on NPC diplomatic trips were
presented to the meeting for review.  
</P>
