<HEADLINE> S. Africa Destroys Small Arms </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, July 6 (Xinhua) -- The South African Department
of Defence destroyed 5,000 small arms at a scrap processing
facility here on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Acting Chief General of the National Defence Force Gilbert
Ramano said the government was well aware of international
concerns over the proliferation of small arms in South Africa and
the increased need to take progressive steps to stop it.
</P>
<P>
By June 28 this year, he said, 60,000 small arms of various
calibres, previously stored in the military inventories, had been
destroyed.
</P>
<P>
