<HEADLINE> Germany Wins Right to Host 2006 World Cup Finals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, July 6 (Xinhua) -- FIFA president Sepp Blatter
announced on Thursday that Germany were awarded the 2006 World Cup
soccer finals over South Africa.
</P>
<P>
Blatter announced the decision at a news conference after a
meeting of the 24-member FIFA executive to choose between four
candidates for the finals.
</P>
<P>
England and Morocco had been eliminated after the first two
rounds of voting.
</P>
<P>
It will be the second time that Germany has staged the
tournament, though the first as a united country. West Germany
hosted the finals in 1974. 
</P>
