<HEADLINE> Germany to Host FIFA 2006 World Cup Finals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, July 6 (Xinhua) -- Germany has won the four-nation race
to host the 2006 World Cup finals, FIFA President Blatter
announced today at the international football federation's
headquarters in Zurich.
</P>
<P>
Germany did not beat South Africa until the final round of
voting in which Germany won 12 votes to 11 with one abstention.
</P>
<P>
Morocco went out in the first round after collecting only three
votes and England in the second round having picked up two votes
at that stage from the 24-member executive committee of the FIFA.
</P>
<P>
A fifth candidate, Brazil, withdrew from the competition, only
one day before the FIFA's final decision. 
</P>
</TEXT>
