<HEADLINE> Beijing to Host Asian-Pacific Cocktail-Mixing Match </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 6 (Xinhua) -- The 2000 Asian-Pacific cocktail-
mixing match is scheduled to be held here July 23-25.
</P>
<P>
Mixologists from China, the Republic of Korea, Indonesia,
Malaysia, the Philippines and Australia will gather at Friday's
Restaurant to make colorful cocktails, according to general
manager Sun Dayu.
</P>
<P>
The profession of mixologists has become more and more
attractive for Chinese young people due to the rapid development
of hotels and bars in the country. At the same time, China's labor
administration department now requires that hopeful mixologists be
systematically trained and acquire related professional
certificates.
</P>
<P>
Friday's Restaurant, founded in New York in 1965, established
its first China branch in Beijing in 1995.
</P>
<P>
Friday's has decided to open a third restaurant in Beijing in
Zhongguancun, known as China's Silicon Valley, this year, said Sun.
</P>
