<HEADLINE> 10 Student Volunteers Join Army </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 6 (Xinhua) -- The General Armament Department of
the Chinese People's Liberation Army recently enlisted ten new
graduates of the China Science and Technology University, who
volunteered to join the army.
</P>
<P>
The students are the first group of university graduates to
join the army after the university and the PLA General Armament
Department signed an agreement on supplying graduates for the army
last year.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese government recently decided that a number of non-
army-run universities and colleges will also train students that
are fit to serve as officers in the army. China Science and
Technology University is one of the schools involved in the
program.
</P>
<P>
The university awarded a prize of 1,000 yuan for each of the
ten who volunteered to join the army.  
</P>
