<HEADLINE> Air China Opens Beijing-Auckland Route </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 6 (Xinhua) -- Air China, the country's flagship,
has opened a new route to New Zealand's biggest city, Auckland.
</P>
<P>
Currently, Air China flies to Auckland on Wednesdays and
Saturdays, and back to Beijing on Thursdays and Sundays. It will
add a Tuesday flight to the route by the end of October.
</P>
<P>
The route is 11,960 km, and takes about 15 hours.
</P>
<P>
In recent years, Sino-New Zealand cooperation and exchanges
have been on the rise, especially since the opening of the tourist
market of the South Pacific country to Chinese visitors.
</P>
<P>
Business and tourism activities have increased sharply, and
trips involving 50,000 people were recorded between the two
countries last year, statistics show. 
