<HEADLINE> SmarTone to Pioneer Broadband Immersive Visualization Technology in HK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 6 (Xinhua) -- SmarTone Broadband Services, the
Internet services arm of communications services provider SmarTone,
Thursday announced an alliance with IT infrastructure services
provider Horky.Com Inc to deliver Hong Kong's first "Immersive
Visualization Technology" to businesses and corporations.
</P>
<P>
The service, which will be fully launched in Hong Kong in the
next two months, will enable users to obtain a real-life, high-
quality 3D viewing experience in a web-based navigable environment,
and offers a 360-degree virtual panoramic experience.
</P>
<P>
Unlike conventional flat images, the "virtual object display"
technology to be launched by SmarTone will present to customers
pictures of products with features and specifications for
customers reference, unfolding the characters of products by
displaying them in 3D.
</P>
<P>
The 360-degree virtual tour technology will enable users to
access the interior design and facility of house, take a tour of
different scenery and exhibition center, which will be a great
help in on-line house selling.
</P>
<P>
"Virtual mall" technology will undoubtedly appeal to many shop
goers. With this new technology, users can easily make a virtual
tour to a shop. When the user selects the shop location, virtual
tour of the shop would display on the screen with a 360-degree
panoramic view.
</P>
<P>
If the user is interested in the mobile phone products, all he
needs to do is to click his mouse, then the image of the mobile
phone will appear and rotate automatically. 
</P>
</TEXT>
