<HEADLINE> Angolan Foreign Minister Leaves for Portugal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, July 6 (Xinhua) -- Angolan Foreign Minister Joao
Miranda left here for Lisbon on Thursday for a two-day visit to
Portugal with a view to strengthening bilateral relations.
</P>
<P>
According to a source with the Angolan presidency, during the
visit, Miranda will hold talks with his Portuguese counterpart
Jaime Gama, and also meet with Prime Minister Antonio Guterres and
President Jorge Sampaio.
</P>
<P>
The talks and meetings are expected to focus on the 2000-2002
Indicative Cooperation Program, which is scheduled to be signed
into effect on Friday, as well as on the strengthening of
bilateral ties in the future.
</P>
<P>
According to the source, Miranda will give a message of the
Angolan President Jose dos Santos to the Portuguese President
Sampaio, which discusses the relations between the two countries,
the political and military situation in Angola, and the prospects
for peace in the war-torn country.
</P>
<P>
The Angolan president meanwhile left Luanda on Wednesday for
three weeks of holidays in France. 
