<HEADLINE> Ningxia Hosts Tourism Commodities Show </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YINCHUAN, July 6 (Xinhua) -- A tourism commodities exhibition
opened today in Yinchuan, capital of northwest China's Ningxia Hui
Autonomous Region, attracting more than 1,800 Chinese and overseas
business people
</P>
<P>
The five-day event, jointly sponsored by the National Tourism
Administration and the local governments, is a part of the 2000
China Ningxia Yellow River International Tourism Festival to be
held here soon.
</P>
<P>
More than 120 items from favorite tourist spots, including
terra-cotta warriors from Xi'an, copper handicrafts from Xinjiang,
and porcelain from Jingdezhen, are displayed in 238 booths at the
exhibition.
</P>
