<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 6 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong stocks closed up 15.32
points, or 0.09 percent, at 16,489.59 Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Property stocks supported the market as Chief Executive Tung
Chee Hwa announced the abolition of the ambitious public housing
plan, while China-related shares and second-line stocks lost
notably during the trading.
</P>
<P>
Of the four sub-indices, Finance and Utilities dropped 0.52
percent and 0.96 percent, but Properties and Industry &AMP; Commerce
rose 1.17 percent and 0.20 percent respectively.
</P>
<P>
The turnover was 12.273 billion HK dollars (1.573 billion U.S.
dollars), compared to Wednesday's 12.861 billion HK dollars (1.649
billion U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
China-related stocks ended lower with the Hang Seng China
Enterprises Index down 2.68 percent and the Hang Seng China-
Affiliated Corp Index down 3.23 percent.
</P>
<P>
The Hang Seng IT Index and the Hang Seng IT Portfolio Index
also decreased by 0.66 percent and 2.61 percent respectively.
</P>
</TEXT>
