<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Macao Hosts Forum on Classical Chinese Poetic Form </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, July 6 (Xinhua) -- A three-day international forum on
the study of ci, a classical Chinese poetic form popular about 1,
000 years ago, was opened here Thursday at the University of Macao.
</P>
<P>
Attending the forum are 35 scholars from Canada, the Republic
of Korea, Singapore and China's inland areas, Hong Kong, Macao and
Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
The art of ci is a key part of the Chinese culture. It conforms
to certain tunes with strict tonal patterns and rhyme schemes in
fix numbers of lines and words. It originated in the Tang Dynasty
(618-907) and fully developed in the Song Dynasty (960-1279).
</P>
<P>
Over the past century, several generations of scholars have
managed to enrich the study of ci and more scholars around the
world are charmed by the poetic treasures.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
