<HEADLINE> Communal Clash Kills Four in Indonesia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, July 6 (Xinhua) -- At least four people were killed
and dozens of houses set ablaze in a communal conflict in Kumai
subdistrict, Indonesia's Central Kalimantan province, on Thursday,
Antara news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
It said that the unrest was sparked by a clash between Madurese
(migrant from Madura island, East Java province) and Malay workers
at illicit timber industries at Kumai port, some 450 kilometers
from Palangka Raya, capital of the province.
</P>
<P>
"One of the dead victim was killed by a molotov cocktail
explosion," the agency said, adding that the regional police had
deployed one Mobile Brigade platoon at the location.
</P>
<P>
It also said that local police and the military have blocked
the location to prevent the clash from spreading. 
</P>
