Among the 26 funds on the Shanghai and Shenzhen markets, four
rose, seven remained unchanged and the rest declined. As to the
five funds that dropped more than one percent, Fund Jintai fell 1.
69 percent and the other four were all restructured funds. In
particular, Fund Tongzhi, Fund Yuze and Fund Zhujiang descended 7.
2 percent, 4.03 percent and 2.4 percent respectively.
</P>
<P>
The four funds that rose today include Fund Xinghua, Fund
Hanxing, Fund Pufeng and Fund Jintai. Fund Xinghua, which rose 1.7
percent today, may have something to do with the Bird Co., Ltd.
which made its debut on the Shanghai Stock Exchange and had its
share priced at more than 35 yuan today.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
