<DOCNO> XIE20000706.0202 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese T-bond Market Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 6 (Xinhua) -- Chinese treasury bonds market saw
broad but moderate pickups today, with trading volume on the
market expanding by 390 million yuan to 48 billion yuan compared
with Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The most active performer on the market, the 10-year 010004
with the interest rate floating by 0.62 percentage points above
the benchmark interest rate on one-year deposits, gained the most
by closing 0.20 percent higher at 101.94 yuan.
</P>
<P>
Bond 000696, an 11.83 percent bond due 2006, ended the session
up 0.15 percent, or 0.21 yuan at 142.65 yuan, pressing the yield
down 0.03 percentage points to 3.81 percent. All the other bonds
finished up less than 0.10.
</P>
<P>
The Export and Import Bank of China (Eximbank) issued five
billion yuan (602 million US dollars) worth of financial bonds on
the interbank bond market on Wednesday. The basic interest spread
was set at 0.555 percent. As the current one-year rate for
deposits at China's financial institutions stands at 2.25 percent,
the nominal annual interest rate for the bonds is 2.805 percent
before the central People's Bank of China (PBOC) revises the one-
year rate.
</P>
<P>
The issuance was the first time the policy bank chose a
floating rate to circumvent interest rate risks, marking major
progress in its market-orientated bond issue reform.
</P>
<P>
Thirty-nine financial institutions, including commercial banks,
insurance companies and urban and rural credit co-operatives,
entered bids, oversubscribing the offer by more than six times and
demonstrating the abundance of funds held by the bidders.
</P>
<P>
Though the new financial bond issuance was on the inter-bank
market, it has drained some money from current treasuries and
partly explained for the thin T-bond trade.
</P>
<P>
Today the trade volume on three-day, seven-day, 14-day and 28-
day repo transactions climbed by 4.73 billion yuan to 6.74 billion
yuan. However, the interest rate on the three-day transaction
edged down slightly by 0.05 percentage points to 3.75 percent.
</P>
</TEXT>
