<HEADLINE> Shanghai B-share Market Down at Thursday Close </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 6 (Xinhua) -- The Shanghai B-share market
remained bearish throughout the Thursday session, gradually
widening its early losses in late trading on mounting selling
pressure.
</P>
<P>
The B-share index dropped 1.17 points, or 2.11 percent, to 54.
37 at the close.
</P>
<P>
Turnover extended to 15.14 million U.S. dollars(RMB 125.66
million), compared with 12.30 million U.S. dollars on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The selling pressure increased late in the session as investors
continued to fret about corporate earnings and could turn nowhere
else to determine the direction, said Homeway, China's leading on-
line financial and securities advisory company.
</P>
<P>
Declining issues outpaced advancing shares by 44 to 3, with
seven unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Sh Refrig Comp rose 3.81 percent to 0.118 U.S. dollar, while
Rubber Belt inched up 0.78 percent to 0.260 U.S. dollar.
</P>
<P>
ST Steel Tube slipped 4.84 percent to 0.118 U.S. dollar, while
Shanghai Hero fell 4.80 percent to 0.238 U.S. dollar.
</P>
<P>
The market will continue to trade in a narrow range and with a
negative bias as broad-based weakness has been too much for the
market to overcome, said Homeway analysts. Many investors may want
to sell positions and head to the sidelines to wait for some
direction towards the end of the week. 
</P>
</TEXT>
