<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shenzhen A-share Market Edges Down </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 6 (Xinhua) -- The Shenzhen composite index closed
at 594 points on Thursday, down 2.2 points or 0.37 percent from
the last close. The sub-index closed at 4704.47 points, 30.79
points or 0.65 percent lower than that of yesterday.
</P>
<P>
Turnover was 9.21 billion yuan (1.1 billion US dollars), 4.5
percent more than yesterday's 8.81 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
The Shenzhen composite index edged down due to the profit
taking pressure, following yesterday's rebound. Four new A shares
made their debuts and two new company issued shares on the
Shanghai and Shenzhen stock markets today, and the IPO market
drained some money away from the secondary market, according to
Homeway, China's leading on-line financial and securities advisory
company.
</P>
<P>
Another two companies will issue A shares tomorrow through the
Shanghai and Shenzhen stock exchanges. The fast pace of IPOs made
the investors turn negative on the market, Homeway said.
</P>
<P>
Chengzhi Shareholding Co. Ltd. and Ningxia ST. Edenweiss Co.
Ltd. made their debuts today. They were also the top gainers with
prices up 168.69 percent and 131.16 percent to 26.6 yuan and 19.
88 yuan per share respectively, compared to their offering prices
of 9.9 yuan and 8.6 yuan per share.
</P>
<P>
Hainan Qingqi Haiyao Holdings Co., Ltd. was the biggest loser.
Its price dropped 8.29 percent to 8.3 yuan per share, hit by
selling pressure.
</P>
<P>
The market is likely to move around the 594-point level
tomorrow, analysts with Homeway said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
