<DOCNO> XIE20000706.0216 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shanghai A-share Market Edges Down </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 6 (Xinhua) -- The Shanghai composite index closed
at 1900.68 points on Thursday, down 8.51 points or 0.45 percent
from the last close.
</P>
<P>
The total trading volume was 8.38 billion yuan (1 billion U.S.
dollars), 5 percent more than the previous session's 7.97 billion
yuan, according to Homeway, China's leading on-line financial and
securities advisory company.
</P>
<P>
The Shanghai composite index edged down due to the profit
taking pressure, after Wednesday's rebound. Four new A shares made
their debuts and two new companies issued shares on the Shanghai
and Shenzhen stock markets today. So the IPOs market drained some
money away from the secondary market.
</P>
<P>
Tomorrow, another two companies will issue their A shares on-
line through the Shanghai and Shenzhen stock exchanges. The fast
pace of IPOs made investors turn negative on the market.
</P>
<P>
Two newcomers, Kaile Plastic Pipe Material (Group) Co., Ltd.
and Ningbo Bird Co., Ltd. were the top gainers today. Their prices
rose 141.35 percent and 119.38 percent to 22.88 yuan and 35.1 yuan
respectively, from their offering prices of 9.48 yuan and 16 yuan
per share.
</P>
<P>
Yibin Paper Industry Co., Ltd. was the biggest loser with its
price down 9.56 percent to 11.83 yuan per share, hit by selling
pressure.
</P>
<P>
The market is likely to test the support line at the 1900-point
level tomorrow, Homeway analysts said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
