<DOCNO> XIE20000706.0217 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Illegal Rat Poison Dominates Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 6 (Xinhua) -- A recent survey in 10 provinces and
municipalities shows that types of rat poison containing lethal
ingredients are easily available in the local market.
</P>
<P>
Of the 116 rat poisons surveyed, 74 percent contain potentially
deadly chemicals that are prohibited by the Chinese authorities.
</P>
<P>
According to the investigation carried out by the Poisoning
Control Center of the Chinese Academy of Preventive Medical
Science, 95 percent of the poisons on sale have not been
registered at government departments concerned or list no warning
on their label.
</P>
<P>
Since February 5, this year's Chinese Lunar New Year's Day,
more than 1,000 local people have accidentally ingested rat poison,
according to the center. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
