<HEADLINE> China's Listed Companies Hit 1,004 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 6 (Xinhua) -- With the listing of Ningbo Bird and
four other stocks on the Shanghai and Shenzhen bourses today, the
number of China's listed companies has topped the expected height
of 1,000 to hit 1,004.
</P>
<P>
China Securities noted that only eight stocks were listed on
China's first stock exchange when it was established in Shanghai
ten years ago.
</P>
<P>
Over the decade, the listed companies raised nearly 400 billion
yuan from the stock market.
</P>
<P>
As of Wednesday, outstanding stocks listed on the two bourses
were worth more than 1.3 trillion yuan, accounting for 16 percent
of China's gross national product in 1999.
</P>
<P>
By mid-June, there were more than 50 million investors with
accounts on the two bourses, about 10 million more than a year ago.
</P>
</TEXT>
