<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shenzhen B-share Market down at Thursday Close </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 6 (Xinhua) -- The Shenzhen B-share market index
ran on another losing streak and easily breached the
psychologically important 110 points in the morning as selling
pressures mounted up.
</P>
<P>
The B-share index plunged 2.99 points, or 2.68 percent, to
close narrowly off its session lows at 108.56.
</P>
<P>
Turnover broadened to 141.30 million HK dollars (RMB149.78
million), which was 75.82 million HK dollars or 115.79 percent
more than Wednesday's total.
</P>
<P>
Foshan Huaxin Packaging Co. Ltd rose as much as 20.24 percent
in its debut on the Shenzhen Stock Exchange, amid the investor
enthusiasm for the first new issue of B-shares foreigners can buy
in two years on the exchange, according to Homeway, China's
leading on-line financial and securities advisory company.
</P>
<P>
The company's successful listing helped lift investor interest
in two other initial share sales by Chinese companies, which was
in the meantime draining money from those already-listed shares
and left the door open to a rather steep southward move in the
market.
</P>
<P>
Losers overwhelmingly beat gainers by 49 to 5, with one
unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Among other advancers, Shzh Tellus rose 1.74 percent to 1.75 HK
dollars, while ST Pro &AMP; ResDev added 0.81 percent to 1.25 HK
dollars.
</P>
<P>
Wuhan Boiler cut 6.54 percent to 1.43 HK dollars, while Chiwan
Base shed 6.27 percent to 2.39 HK dollars.
</P>
<P>
The market will continue to trade within a narrow range and
with a negative bias, analysts with Homeway said. Investors may
either want to sell positions to leave money for the purchase of
new shares or head to the sidelines to wait for some direction
towards the end of the week. 
</P>
</TEXT>
