Treasury to extract nine articles, including some seen as key
elements, of the proposed Ben-Bassat Committee tax reform
recommendations, Israeli Finance Minister Avraham Shochat said
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The abridged plan takes into account the changes demanded by the
Histadrut labor federation - which threatened to call a general
strike if its demands were not met - and by other pressure groups.
</P>
<P>
Shochat said that "in financial terms, 70 percent of the
original plan remains, but a great deal more remains in terms of
quality." The tax reform plan was drawn up by a blue-ribbon
commission of 11 experts headed by Finance Ministry Director-
General Avi Ben-Bassat. 
</P>
