<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, July 6 (Xinhua) -- The Bangkok Metropolitan
Administration (BMA) will organize the Bangkok Day in Moscow,
aimed at publicizing Thai arts and cultures, and tourism in the
country, the Thai News Agency (TNA) said on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Pol. Sub. Lt. Kriengsak Lohachala, Deputy Permanent Secretary
for the BMA Kriengsak Lohachala was quoted as saying that the
planned Bangkok Day would be organized between August 21 and 25 at
the Cultural Center in Moscow.
</P>
<P>
Four categories of activities would be launched at the five-day
event, including shows of Thai arts and cultures from all regions
of the country, technical campaigns to promote the Thai tourism in
Moscow, an exhibition on Thai ways of life, and displays of Thai
products and handicrafts, he disclosed.
</P>
<P>
Thai canned and dried, as well as crafted fruits would also be
demonstrated at the event with the cooperation of the Thai
Ministry of Commerce, he said.
</P>
<P>
The Russian government would also organize the Moscow Day in
Bangkok later this year, aimed to promote the exchange of arts and
cultures between the two countries, said the senior BMA official.
