<HEADLINE> Chinese Army Forms First Team of Flying Doctors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 6 (Xinhua) -- A newly-formed squad of flying
doctors of the Chinese People's Liberation Army (PLA) was
airdropped for the first time in a recent military exercise.
</P>
<P>
The successful drill marks a new step forward in the
development of the PLA's airborne medical services, according to
PLA sources.
</P>
<P>
In the initial phase of the activity, dozens of medical staff
with medical equipment and small transport vehicles were dropped
aground an airport, and ten minutes later, a simple field clinic
was set up and medical treatment began.
</P>
<P>
Then 30 minutes later, three aircraft carrying a team of
doctors and more sophisticated medical equipment landed. A
multifunctional field clinic soon appeared, with different wards
of "injured" soldiers housed in various tents.
</P>
<P>
Computers were involved in the activity, giving doctors the
opportunity to consult with colleagues at rear hospitals afar
about treatment for severe injuries.  
</P>
