<HEADLINE> ASEAN Experts' Meetings on Herbal Plants, Forestry Held in Myanmar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, July 6 (Xinhua) -- Two expert group meetings of the
Association of Southeast Asian Nations (ASEAN) on herbal and
medicinal plants, and on research and development for forest
products began here Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The two-day meetings are discussing exchange of comprehensive
data on herbal and medicinal plants, submission of five species of
medicinal plants and profile of selected family and harmonization
of data-base format, and establishment of database on ASEAN herbal
and medicinal plants.
</P>
<P>
Documentation of research and development information and
directory, cultivation, propagation and selection of elite genetic
material, and photochemical screening of flora for the therapeutic
aromatic value will also be discussed.
</P>
