<HEADLINE> Sweltering Weather Sweeps Across Albania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, July 5 (Xinhua) -- Albania has been suffering a
sweltering weather over the past few days, with the highest
temperature reaching 42 degrees Centigrade.
</P>
<P>
The hot spell started from Monday, as a result of a hot air
flow from southeast, and has swept all major cities in Albania in
the last few days. Temperatures in the southern city of
Gjirokastra hit an all-time high in the last four decades.
</P>
<P>
All local TV stations are showing programs about how to deal
with hot weather, which has caused much inconvenience.
</P>
<P>
Public places are left almost deserted and kids are reluctant
to leave fountains in downtown areas.
</P>
<P>
Worse still, many people, old and young, including babies, have
become sick. Over the past three days, a Tirana general hospital
received 120 to 130 toddlers a day for heat-related illness.
</P>
<P>
The hot weather is expected to be a little better in the days
ahead, with the temperature dropping by two to three degrees, the
Albanian Meteorological Observatory forecast on Wednesday.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
