<HEADLINE> Azerbaijani President Visits Austria </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VIENNA, July 5 (Xinhua) -- Azerbaijani President Heydar Aliyev,
at the invitation of his Austrian counterpart Thomas Klestil, paid
an official working visit to Austria on Tuesday and Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Aliyev informed the Austrian president about discussions held
between Azerbaijan and Armenia and efforts made by Azerbaijan in
settling his country's dispute with Armenia over Nagorno-Karabakh.
</P>
<P>
The Azerbaijani president hoped that Austria, the EU, the
Organization for Security and Cooperation in Europe (OSCE) and
other international organizations would be more engaged in seeking
a solution to the dispute.
</P>
<P>
Klestil pointed out the geostrategic importance of the Caucasus
country, saying Austria is paying more attention to this region as
current presidency-holder of the OSCE.
</P>
<P>
The two presidents agreed that their countries have a big room
to further develop bilateral relations in politics, economy and
culture.
</P>
<P>
A series of agreements in the fields of taxation, investment
and aviation were signed during Aliyev's visit.
</P>
<P>
Aliyev invited foreign countries including Austria to invest in
Azerbaijan, saying his country is rich in natural resources and
has a big economic potential.
</P>
<P>
The visiting president also held meetings with Austrian
National Council President Heinz Fischer, Austrian Chancellor
Wolfgang Schuessel and Foreign Minister and present OSCE President
Benita Ferrero-waldner. 
</P>
