<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Coal Export Expanding </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 6 (Xinhua) -- China exported 20.93 million tons
of coal in the first five months this year, up 45.6 percent over
the same period of last year, according to the State
Administration of Coal Industry.
</P>
<P>
The increase of coal export has effectively eased the domestic
situation of coal supply exceeding demand, a senior official with
the State Administration of Coal said.
</P>
<P>
China has maintained favorable growth in coal export since the
beginning of this year and it expects to export a record 45
million tons by the end of this year, the official said.
</P>
<P>
He noted that China is expanding coal export and world market
shares by stepping up construction of export coal production bases
and improving coal quality.
</P>
<P>
The official stressed that to expand coal export is of great
significance for the reduction of coal stockpile, the balance
between coal supply and demand and the sustainable development of
the country's coal industry.  
</P>
</TEXT>
