<BODY>
<HEADLINE> One Killed, Three Wounded in McDonald's Shooting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUDAPEST, July 5 (Xinhua) -- One was killed and three wounded
when a man opened fire in a McDonald's restaurant in Budapest,
police said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Police said the 25-year-old man walked into the restaurant in
downtown Budapest at about 10 minutes to midnight Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
He stayed in the men's room for a few minutes before he came
out to shoot at customers. This sent frightened customers and
waiters fleeing to the street. The man chased them and gunned down
another.
</P>
<P>
Police arrested the man a few hundred meters from the
restaurant.
</P>
<P>
One victim died soon in hospital. Two of the wounded are in
fatal condition.
</P>
<P>
It was the most serious shooting event in Budapest since 1997.
</P>
</TEXT>
