<HEADLINE> Highlights of Major Beijing-Based Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 6 (Xinhua) -- The following are today's
highlights of major Beijing-based newspapers:
</P>
<P>
People's Daily
</P>
<P>
-- Chinese President Jiang Zemin called in Dushanbe on
Wednesday for fleshing out and perfecting the "Shanghai Five"
mechanism and deepening cooperation among China, Tajikistan,
Russia, Kazakhstan and Kyrgyzstan in security, trade and other
international arenas.
</P>
<P>
Jiang made the call at an annual summit meeting commonly known
as the "Shanghai Five" summit.
</P>
<P>
-- The adoption of the rule of law regarding the promotion and
popularization of the common language is of great importance for
safeguarding national unity, strengthening solidarity between
people of different ethnic groups and boosting social and economic
development.
</P>
<P>
