the National People's Congress at a meeting held Wednesday to
discuss a draft law on the national common language.
</P>
<P>
Xinhua Daily Telegraph
</P>
<P>
-- Chinese President Jiang Zemin arrived at Ashkhabad,
Turkmenistan, Wednesday evening for a state visit at the
invitation of Turkmenistan President Saparmurad Niyazov.
</P>
<P>
Niyazov hosted a red-carpet ceremony to welcome Jiang, the
first Chinese head of state to visit this central Asian country.
Jiang, accompanied by Niyazov, inspected the guards of honor at
the airport.
</P>
<P>
-- A Chinese party leader has urged town and township officials
to increase transparency of government work and promote democracy,
so as to boost rural reform and stability.
</P>
<P>
Wei Jianxing, Standing Committee member of the Political Bureau
of the Communist Party Central Committee, made the remarks during
his study tour in Tianjin, 100 kilometers east of Beijing, from
July 2-4.
</P>
<P>
China Daily
</P>
<P>
-- Chinese President Jiang Zemin told Russian President
Vladimir Putin Wednesday that China supports Russia's position
that the integrity of the Anti-ballistic Missile Treaty must be
maintained.
</P>
<P>
Jiang's remarks came at the first meting of the two heads of
state since Putin was elected president three months ago.
</P>
<P>
-- Visiting Chinese Premier Zhu Rongji met in Hague Wednesday
with Dutch Queen Beatrix Wilhelmina Armgard and parliament leaders.
</P>
<P>
Zhu had brief talks with the parliament leaders, First Chamber
President Koethals Altes and Second Chamber's First Vice-President
Frans Weisglas.  
</P>
</TEXT>
