<DOCNO> XIE20000706.0328 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Jilin Province to Build "Optical Valley" </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGCHUN, June 6 (Xinhua) -- China has started to build an
optical electronics industrial park in this capital of Jilin
Province, in the northeast.
</P>
<P>
The park, to cover 2,120,000 sq m, will focus on the optical
electronics, instruments and information technology industries. It
will include development and research buildings, office buildings,
workshops for making optical materials and precision instruments.
</P>
<P>
The park, nicknamed "optical valley", is being set up by the
Institute of Optical Precision Machinery and Physics, the branch
of the Chinese Academy of Sciences in Changchun and the Changchun
Economic Development Zone.
</P>
<P>
With a total investment budget of 18 billion yuan (about 2.2
billion US dollars), the park will be constructed by two phases
over a period of five years and hopes to achieve a yearly revenue
of more than 30 billion yuan (about 3.6 billion US dollars) after
completion.
</P>
<P>
Wang Daheng, a leading optical scientist, said that the park
will be a center of the national research on optics and trade in
related products. It will also, hopefully, become a research and
production base of optical devices and an exchange center for
international scientific communications.
</P>
<P>
Analysts said that the country's optical electronics industry
will create 5,000 billion US dollars in revenue within this
century.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, other cities in China, such as Shanghai, Wuhan and
Guangzhou, are now constructing "optical valleys" of their own.
</P>
</TEXT>
