will be held next Tuesday in the United States.
</P>
<P>
Sharansky, whose party has four seats in the Knesset
(Parliament), blamed Barak for keeping the coalition party leaders
in the dark about the ongoing Israeli-Palestinian final-status
talks. He also accused Barak of making too many concessions to the
Palestinians regarding territorial transfer. (Israel-Coalition-
Resignation) 
