<HEADLINE> Rolls-Royce Awards EDS $2.1 Billion IT Contract </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, July 6 (Xinhua) - Rolls-Royce plc announced Thursday
that it has agreed to extend its successful technology, services
and consulting relationship with EDS.
</P>
<P>
Rolls-Royce has awarded EDS 2.1 billion US dollars contract to
provide global information technology services and business
solutions, covering e-business, consulting and supply chain
management.
</P>
<P>
"EDS has become our strategic partner in building a truly
global, integrated company," said Chris Hole, Director of
Procurement, Rolls-Royce plc. "This agreement will bring new
levels of value and benefit to Rolls-Royce."
</P>
<P>
The focus for the initial phase of the new agreement between
Rolls-Royce and EDS will be on enabling business integration and
work-share collaboration, according to the announcement.
</P>
<P>
This will include e-businesss solutions, with plans currently
for three portals covering the supply chain, design collaboration
and corporate information; consulting-led business initiatives for
the global supply chain; innovative Application Service Provision
offerings and further improvements in IT services, it said.
</P>
<P>
EDS already provides IT services to Rolls-Royce across the UK
and North America. In addition, EDS is responsible for Rolls-Royce
IT infrastructure, network, systems and applications, and end-user
support, it added. 
</P>
