<HEADLINE> Sao Paulo Stocks Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRASILIA, July 6 (Xinhua) -- Stocks on the Sao Paulo Securities
Exchange, the largest in Latin America, closed up Thursday with
the key Bovespa Index increasing by 1.24 percent to 17,348 points
from Wednesday's 17,134 points.
</P>
<P>
Dealers exchanged 384 million U.S. dollars against 461 million
dollars  in the previous session.
</P>
<P>
The exchange rate of the local currency, the real, stood at 1.
80 for one U.S. dollar, maintaining the same as Wednesday.
</P>
