<HEADLINE> European Stock Markets End Mixed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, July 6 (Xinhua) -- Europe's leading stock markets
closed mixed Thursday as telecom companies powered higher behind
mobile-phone leader Vodafone AirTouch.
</P>
<P>
Market heavyweight Vodafone lifted London's FTSE 100 firmly
above 6400, outweighing a weaker start on Wall Street. The index
closed up 37.1 points or 0.58 percent to 6419.6.
</P>
<P>
Software and computer consultants weakened a day after a spate
of earnings warnings from high-tech companies in the US Logic led
the list of FTSE losers, falling 7.7 percent, CMG slipped 3
percent and Misys dropped 3.7 percent.
</P>
<P>
In the defense sector, BAE System added 3.4 percent after
aircraft maker Airbus Industrie said it has received" fantastic
interest in its planned super-jumbo A3XX plane.
</P>
<P>
Outside the FTSE 100, online bank Egg fell 5 percent.The stock
dipped further below its IPO price of 160 pence as investors
became more pessimistic about its competitive strength against
traditional banks.
</P>
<P>
German shares ended lower, weighed down by falls in small and
large cap technology stocks amid concerns about earnings in the
sector. the DAX index ended 0.15 percent or 10.64 lower at 6915.09.
</P>
<P>
The Paris Bourse ended marginally lower as France Telecom's
rally mostly offset the bearish mood in bank and"new economy"
stocks. The CAC 40 ended with a drop of 8.73 points, or 0.1
percent, at 6453.97. 
</P>
</TEXT>
