<HEADLINE> Nicaraguan Earthquake Leaves People Wounded </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANAGUA, July 6 (Xinhua) -- A series of strong earth tremors on
Thursday have caused some people wounded and destroyed several
houses in Nicaragua, according to official sources here.
</P>
<P>
An earthquake measuring 5.9 degree on the Richter scale jolted
Thursday Nicaragua, causing panic all over the Central American
country.
</P>
<P>
The tremor was registered at 13:30 local time (19:30 GMT).
</P>
<P>
The epicenter was in the Lake of Apoyo, in the Granada
department, some 36 kilometers southeast from the capital city of
Managua, with depth of only one kilometer.
</P>
<P>
People of the capital went out from their houses or apartments
due to the panic. The earth movement was also felt in the
departments along the Pacific coast, such as Carazo, Chinandege,
Granad, Esteli and Masaya.
</P>
<P>
Telephone connections were cut in some parts of the country,
but recovered quickly. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
