<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Wall Street Stocks End Mixed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, July 6 (Xinhua) -- Wall Street stocks ended mixed
Thursday with the blue chip stocks falling on worries about
corporate earnings. But the tech shares rose.
</P>
<P>
The Dow Jones industrial average closed down 2.13 at 10,481.47,
extending its loss of 77.07 points Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The technology heavy Nasdaq composite index rose 97.47 at 3,960.
57, bouncing back from a steep drop of 128.83 points in the
previous session.
</P>
<P>
Broader stock indicators were also higher. The Standard &AMP; Poor'
s 500 index rose 10.44 at 1,456.67.
</P>
<P>
The Dow index fell after a Merrill Lynch analyst said companies
that do business with IBM are struggling and may cut back on
orders. The comments sparked fears that IBM, the Dow's component,
will miss earnings expectations in the second quarter, dragging
the company's shares lower for the fourth session in a row.
</P>
<P>
But the Nasdaq composite rose as investors rushed in the market
to look for those stocks that battered in the recent sessions. The
bargain-hunting drove Oracle and Altera higher.
</P>
<P>
The tech shares as well as the blue chips fell Wednesday as a
flurry of profit warnings dominated the market.
</P>
<P>
The NYSE index rose 0.85 at 645.75 and the American Stock
Exchange index rose 6.17 at 927.88. The Russell 2000 index of
smaller companies rose 5.07 at 523.32.
</P>
<P>
Advancing issues outnumbered decliners by a 4-to-3 margin on
the New York Stock Exchange, with 1,652 up, 1,265 down and 446
unchanged.
</P>
<P>
NYSE volume declined to 943.37 million shares from 1.003
billion in the previous session. 
</P>
</TEXT>
